  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nIf 2 users are using different networks (i.e. `BSC` and `Mainnet`), user on Mainnet can request ETH in 1-1 chat, but user on BSC network will get request for `BNB`.\r\nThat can cause confusion for both parts.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nSomething like \"Transaction messages should be only available on `Mainnet`\", actions are not available\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n![photo_2022-09-13 15 59 54 jpeg 2022-09-13 16-01-09](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/189921714-6fa04fb9-2b98-40b5-9701-370008b9b650.png)\r\nSo user can sign and send funds on another network.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1) UserA: request some funds on Mainnet from UserB\r\n2) UserB: switch to any other network and check chat with UserA\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly 13/09/22\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
